title: ACC Falls Data 2007-2019
description:
ACC claims relating to accidents caused by an action categorized as falling (i.e. slipping, tripping, misjudging a step, etc.). OIA: 51599.  The information provided is based on the following criteria/considerations.
The data has been extracted based on the following criteria:
The claim has an accident cause equal to one of the following:
- Loss Balance/Personal Contrl
- Loss of Consciousness/Sleep
- Misjudgement of Support
- Slipping, Skidding on Foo
- Something Giving way Underfoot
- Tripping or Stumbling
The claim was lodged or active in the period between 1 January 2007 and 30 November 2019.  Data were extracted on 1 December 2019.
publisher.name: ACC
distribution.0.title: Falls Data 2007-2019

title: Motor Vehicle Accident claims
description:
ACC claims relating to motor vehicle or road accidents.
The information provided is based on the following criteria/considerations.
The data has been extracted based on the following criteria:
* The claim has is funded under the ACC Motor vehicle fund.
* The claim was lodged or active in the period between 1 July 2011 and 30 June 2018.
* The claim has a cover decision equal to "Accept".
Caveats / Notes:
- Costs provided are exclusive of GST.
- Costs are based on payment date. Payment date may be different to the date of service.
- Accredited employer claims are excluded from the information.
- A financial year is 1 July to 30 June.
- Any instances of client gender, age, ethnicity, or accident location that are missing are not included in the information.
- ACC is reliant on the information a person provides on their ACC45 injury claim form which is completed when they seek medical treatment for their injury.
- Data were extracted on 30 November 2018 and may differ if re-run at a later date.
keywords: ACC, Cars, claims, motor vehicle accident
publisher.name: ACC
distribution.0.title: Motor Vehicle Accidents Data
distribution.1.title: New Motor Vehicle Accidents
distribution.2.title: Active Motor Vehicle Accidents

title: Number of elective surgery requests received for hip labral tears
description:
The data has been extracted for claims where an elective surgery request, with the surgery code HIT50-52, HIT60-62 or HIT70-7, has a service date between 1 July 2013 and 30 June 2019. The data provided was extracted on 18 October 2019 and may differ if re-run at a later date.  In recent years, the hip surgery codes have not been able to be loaded against individual purchase orders. In instances where this has been the case, we have extracted data for elective surgery requests
where the surgery site was hip and the comments field included the key terms arthroscopy and hip/labral or the surgery codes, as mentioned above.
publisher.name: ACC
distribution.0.title: Elective surgery data
